relation: A protein complex that catalyzes the reversible oxidation of glycine. In E. coli, it has four components: dihydrolipoamide dehydrogenase, glycine dehydrogenase (decarboxylating), lipoyl-GcvH-protein and aminomethyltransferase, also known as L, P, H, and T.

A multienzyme complex that catalyzes the reversible oxidation of glycine. In E. coli, it has four components: dihydrolipoamide dehydrogenase, glycine dehydrogenase (decarboxylating), lipoyl-GcvH-protein and aminomethyltransferase.

An enzyme complex composed of aminomethyltransferase and glycine dehydrogenase (decarboxylating). It catalyzes the cleavage of glycine, forming dihydrolipoylprotein, methylenetetrahydrofolate and ammonia.
